    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-05T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-05T06:00:00-05:00" n="381"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C/1007: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tittmann</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-05T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 5, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 5—9:36
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Consulate’s 13, February 1, 4 p.m. The Canadian delegate has addressed a
                    letter to Bourquin in which he states that <pb facs="0321" n="312"
                        xml:id="pg_312"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In the opinion of the Canadian Government it would be desirable for the
                            Organizing Committee to defer the definition of the relationship between
                            the Central Committee and the Advisory Committee on Opium and Other
                            Dangerous Drugs until the latter Committee has had the opportunity to
                            discuss the whole matter at its next meeting in May.</p>
                        <p>Should this suggestion not prove to be acceptable I am instructed to
                            state that the Canadian Government wishes to reserve its position in
                            respect to any changes which might be recommended by the Organizing
                            Committee for the new Central Committee and which might affect the
                            independence and autonomy of the Opium Advisory Committee in the
                            exercise of its administrative and treaty functions.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tittmann</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
